Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}
(or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Cut the @medium tomato{2} into 1cm chunks.

== Caramelised Onion ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring
occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add the @sugar{1} (see pantry for amount) and cook until caramelised,
~{1-2%minutes} more.

Transfer to a small #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

== Glazed Beef ==

Wipe out the frying pan and return to medium-high heat (no oil).

Once the pan is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a spoon to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard
any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's
> cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic to the pan, then stir fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @beef stock paste{10%g}, @water{100%ml} for the sauce and
@tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} (see pantry for both amounts) to the pan, then stir
until combined.

Cook until the beef is glazed and the sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, share the chips between your plates.

Top with the glazed beef, tomatoes and caramelised onions - fries loaded!

Drizzle over the @burger sauce{45%g} and finish with a sprinkle of cheese.

Enjoy!